Twisted's @inlineCallbacks decorator basically does this for you; whenever you yield a deferred (Twisted's representation of an ongoing operation), the rest of the generator is registered as the callback for when the operation is finished.  Your example becomes:<p><pre><code>  @defer.inlineCallbacks
  def A(x):
      x = yield B(x)
      C(x)

  @defer.inlineCallbacks
  def B(x):
      factor = yield AsyncCall()
      defer.returnValue(x * factor)</code></pre>
